<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-11-28T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-11-28T11:00:00-05:00" n="467" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d467">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">851.248/302: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-28T16:00:00+00:00">November 28, 1939—4
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 4:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2844. I communicated the substance of your No. 1443, November 25, 3
                                p.m., gently to Daladier today. He said that he understood but could
                                not escape from the conclusion that it would be essential for me to
                                make such a trip in the month of January. I left the matter
                                there.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>